article.headline: Mann, Flynn propel Bowling Green in Caribbean Classic
article.linkText: Mann, Flynn propel Bowling Green over Texas Arlington
article.story:
CANCUN, Mexico (AP) -- Ali Mann and Amber Flynn scored 16 points
apiece to lead Bowling Green (No. 21 ESPN/USA Today) to a 59-48 win over Texas-Arlington in
the Caribbean Classic Tournament on Wednesday.

The Falcons shot 49 percent from the field and 4-of-11 from the
3-point line in their smallest margin of victory this season.

Mann also had six rebounds and four assists for Bowling Green
(8-2), and Liz Honegger added nine points and six boards. The
Falcons outrebounded Texas-Arlington 36-28.

Tiffeny Riles and LaTosha Duffey led Texas-Arlington (4-7) with
12 points each.

The Mavericks shot 33 percent from the field and made 9-of-17
free throws.

Bowling Green finished the tournament 1-1 after losing 55-46
Tuesday to fourth-ranked Duke. Texas-Arlington also was 1-1, with a
58-54 win over Liberty on the opening day.
